member.name: T:Amazon.S3Outposts.Model.CreateEndpointRequest
member.summary:
Container for the parameters to the CreateEndpoint operation. Amazon S3 on Outposts Access Points simplify managing data access at scale for shared datasets in S3 on Outposts. S3 on Outposts uses endpoints to connect to Outposts buckets so that you can perform actions within your virtual private cloud (VPC). For more information, see Accessing S3 on Outposts using VPC only access points.
This action creates an endpoint and associates it with the specified Outposts.
It can take up to 5 minutes for this action to complete.
Related actions include:
DeleteEndpoint
ListEndpoints

member.name: P:Amazon.S3Outposts.Model.CreateEndpointRequest.AccessType
member.summary:
Gets and sets the property AccessType.
The type of access for the on-premise network connectivity for the Outpost endpoint. To access the endpoint from an on-premises network, you must specify the access type and provide the customer owned IPv4 pool.

member.name: P:Amazon.S3Outposts.Model.CreateEndpointRequest.CustomerOwnedIpv4Pool
member.summary:
Gets and sets the property CustomerOwnedIpv4Pool.
The ID of the customer-owned IPv4 pool for the endpoint. IP addresses will be allocated from this pool for the endpoint.

member.name: P:Amazon.S3Outposts.Model.CreateEndpointRequest.OutpostId
member.summary:
Gets and sets the property OutpostId.
The ID of the AWS Outposts.

member.name: P:Amazon.S3Outposts.Model.CreateEndpointRequest.SecurityGroupId
member.summary:
Gets and sets the property SecurityGroupId.
The ID of the security group to use with the endpoint.

member.name: P:Amazon.S3Outposts.Model.CreateEndpointRequest.SubnetId
member.summary:
Gets and sets the property SubnetId.
The ID of the subnet in the selected VPC. The endpoint subnet must belong to the Outpost that has the Amazon S3 on Outposts provisioned.

member.name: M:Amazon.S3Outposts.AmazonS3OutpostsClient.CreateEndpoint(Amazon.S3Outposts.Model.CreateEndpointRequest)
member.summary:
Amazon S3 on Outposts Access Points simplify managing data access at scale for shared datasets in S3 on Outposts. S3 on Outposts uses endpoints to connect to Outposts buckets so that you can perform actions within your virtual private cloud (VPC). For more information, see Accessing S3 on Outposts using VPC only access points.
This action creates an endpoint and associates it with the specified Outposts.
It can take up to 5 minutes for this action to complete.
Related actions include:
DeleteEndpoint
ListEndpoints
